Kenya Data Plans to Invest in Back-Up System, Bus. Daily Says

-- B y   S a r a h   M c G r e g o r
-- 
2011-06-07T05:41:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-07/kenya-data-plans-to-invest-in-back-up-system-bus-daily-says.html
Kenya Data Networks Ltd.  will invest
2.8 billion shillings ($32 million) in a back-up system for its
fibre-optic cable network to reduce outages,  Business Daily 
reported, citing Chief Technical Officer Bob Lafite.  The company signed a 320 million-shilling agreement with
Israel-based  ECI Telecom Ltd.  to upgrade its network, the
Nairobi-based newspaper reported today.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Sarah McGregor in Nairobi at 
 smcgregor5@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden at 
 barden@bloomberg.net . 